				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is a copy of the revised top 10 list that Danille submitted.
<br />

<br />
Short version:
<br />
1) Improve pet damage output (Pet Issues/Requests) [currently being discussed]
<br />
- Unchanged
<br />
2) Overhaul class specific AA's. [requested more detail]
<br />
- Provided more details
<br />
3) Fix Fire pet [currently being discussed]
<br />
- Unchanged
<br />
4) Improved Damage shield [incorrectly classified as done]
<br />
- Unchanged
<br />
5) Streamline the item summoning process (more target summons) [currently being discussed]
<br />
- Unchanged
<br />
6) Allow suspended pets to zone, OR allow pets to remain with their master while the master is invisible.  (Pet Issues/Requests) [updated request]
<br />
- Changed request, since pets now zone
<br />
7) Improve pet Heals. (Pet Issues/Requests) [currently being discussed]
<br />
- Unchanged
<br />
8) Revamp pet focus availability. (Pet Issues/Requests) [updated request]
<br />
- Changed request, since off-tanking is too broad a term, and related to too many factors besides the pet itself
<br />
9) COH useable in more zones. (make CoTH available in all corpse summoning zones) [currently being discussed]
<br />
- Unchanged
<br />
10) Better utility in groups and raids [detail was requested]
<br />
- Provided more details
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
The Long Version:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 24px; line-height: normal">MAGICIAN TOP TEN </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold">1) Improve pet damage output (Pet Issues/Requests) [currently being discussed]</span></span>
<br />

<br />
First and Foremost, the damage upgrades for pet focuses is, by far, inadequate. Pets do not receive even close to the damage increases that damage and mana foci provide, nor do they scale close in terms of overall melee increases. Additionally, there is a gap between equivalent Ornate-level magician pets, and Time-level magician pets, that Minion of Darkness does not bridge.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">a) Increase the HP of Minion of Darkness to better fall between Summoner's Boon and Minion of Eternity</span>
<br />

<br />
Unfocused Air pet = 3775hp (approx), DPOC= 4200hp (approx), MoD needs to be 4600 (approx), MoE= 5085 (approx), Mancy = MoE.
<br />

<br />
Furthermore, there does not exist a pet focus that bridges the gap between Vex Thal mages and Plane of Time mages. This gap should be fixed by introduing the "Mancy" line of focuses in the Elemental Planes. Pyromancy from Plane of Fire, Aeromancy from Plane of Air, Aquamancy from Plane of Water, Geomancy from Plane of Earth.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">b) Upgrade the max melee damage of focused pets</span>
<br />

<br />
Using air pet as example:
<br />

<br />
Summary:
<br />
Unfocused - 83 damage, level 60 
<br />
Summoner's Boon (Ornate) - 86 damage,  level 61
<br />
Minion of Darkness (Vex Thal) - 97 damage, level 62, needs a HP boost as described above.
<br />
Minion of Eternity (Time) - 108 damage, level 63
<br />
Ritual Summoning (Qvic)- 118 damage, level 64
<br />
Minion of Discord (Tacvi) - 128 damage, level 65
<br />

<br />
Omens of War pets should scale in a similar manner.
<br />
Increasing the maximum melee damage as said above will help ensure pets scale better with focii compared to equivalent level spell focii.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">C) Upgrade the burnout series</span>
<br />

<br />
The haste components do not need to be looked at, it’s the other statistical boosts these buffs provide. In addition, Beastlords can augment their pet with a +75 dex proc buff, whereas Magicians cannot. Somewhere along the way, beastlords overpowered magicians in terms of buffing up the pet. This should be corrected.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Burnout 3</span>
<br />
from 50 str, 13 ac
<br />
to 55 str, 15 ac, 25 atk
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Burnout 4</span>
<br />
from 60 str, 16 ac
<br />
to 30 ac, 40 atk, 75 dex
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Ancient Burnout Blaze</span>
<br />
to 100 str, 60 ac, 60 atk, 75 dex
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Burnout 5</span>
<br />
from 80 str, 40 atk, 22 ac
<br />
to 115 str, 71 ac, 75 atk, 75 dex
<br />
 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">2) Overhaul class specific AA's. [requested more detail]</span>
<br />

<br />
Here are the Mage AA’s that are in need of attention and the detail you requested on Elemental Agility:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">1) Elemental Agility- This AA is broken.</span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Here is the description: (4 / 8 / 12 AA points needed to purchase this ability.
<br />
Increases Magician pet avoidance and mitigation by an approximate 2%, 5%, and 10%).</span>
<br />

<br />
Mages have purchased all three levels of this AA at a cost of 24 AA’s and have noticed no significant change in the pet’s mitigation performance. (Parses taken show that Elemental Agility 3 = 3% less mob accuracy. Mob accuracy goes from 66%ish to 63%ish. Also parsed a 1.5%-2% drop in dps taken by pet, from pre-EA to EA3. Please note that parses have an +/- 3% error factor on results so the pet performance benefit is negligible, if it works at all). This is probably the 2nd worst AA of all in GoD in terms of overall usefulness and cost vs. reward.
<br />

<br />
Link to old parsing info - <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13390" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13390</a>
<br />
(Xalmat is conducting some new parses as we speak.)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">2) Elemental Forms –</span>
<br />
a) They need to be usable on a mount. Remove the illusion component, or allow the illusion component to be removed without losing the full benefit of the buffs.
<br />
b) The levitate component from air form needs to be removed. There are many zones where levitation is not allowed and this currently causes the AA to fail.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">3) Mass Group Buff –</span>
<br />
Mages have one group buff, our Damage Shield (duration 15 minutes). With a recast time of 1 hour and 12 minutes, this AA is virtually useless at present unless you give us a faster recast time or both quick MGB and Spell Casting Reinforcement AA’s. The problem is the 72-minute reuse time is far too long for a situational DS. (Currently, mages are toggling TGB/on and just casting group DS every 15 minutes anyway).
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">4) Quick MGB –</span>
<br />
Asked for this AA above and why don't all classes that have MGB have this?
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">5) Frenzied Burnout –</span>
<br />
Presently has a 72 minutes recast timer. It needs to be lower, on the margin of 9 minutes like a discipline. Or increase the duration to 72 minutes. Even throw in a hasted Frenzied, which reduces the reuse time of this ability by 25% per rank (on-par with hasted Mend).
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">6) Turn Summoned –</span>
<br />
This AA is useless. It resists 90% of the time and no one ever uses it anyway because mages can’t snare. Mages all agree that the fear component needs to be removed, and it should be changed to a "Manaburn type" ability against summoned mobs, minus the draining of your mana pool (or alternatively just a very high DD with very low aggro).
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">7) Elemental Pact –</span>
<br />
(eliminates the need for a regent to be used when making elemental pets, in our case malachite) Needs to remove the need to carry malachite, not just removing the cost. All classes who have this AA want to eliminate the need to carry one regent in their inventory as it takes up a slot that can be sued for something else.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">8) Host of the Elements –</span>
<br />
a) The 5/7 and 9 tiny earth pets that are created when this AA is used, needs to be level 60 so they can enrage. They need more HP to match the Shaman version. AA cost needs to be lowered to 3/3/3. Reuse timer needs to be lowered to 9 minutes, not 22 minutes. Duration needs to be increased to 1 minute, not 30 seconds. 
<br />
b) In addition many mages would like the Host or the Elements AA to be able to summon tiny earth, air, water, fire and monster pets. Currently we only have one form that is available (earth).
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">9) Mend Companion -</span>
<br />
As EQ content has grown and our pets have as well, this AA doesn't do anywhere near enough for the pet anymore. A maximum Mend does, at most, about 50% of the pet's HP, which is barely enough for one melee round in most high level zones (On a fully raid buffed Rathe's Son, this is usually around 25%). The AA is really insufficient if you're using a high HP pet like Rathe's Son, or if any of our 5 pets are focused and/or buffed.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">10) Secondary Forte -</span>
<br />
15 AAs for 2.5% mana preservation. The cost of our most commonly used nuke is Firebolt of Tallon, which costs 500 mana to cast (with no mana preservation items equipped). The mana savings for 15 AA’s comes to 12.5 mana saved. Considering the average lvl 65 mage has a 4500-mana pool, this AA provides a savings of 0.277% per nuke. This is probably the worst AA of all in GoD in terms of overall usefulness and cost vs. reward. At 15 AA’s, our suggestion is to increase the specialization level to 200.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">11) Shared Health -</span>
<br />
Should have much larger range and unlimited damage cap for the duration of the ability. Its rare Magicians and pets are close to each other because mages fight from a ranged position. In fact we often fight from a large distance. Reuse time should be 3 minutes to be equal with Warrior /shield, not 15 minutes. The range needs to be increased from 10 to 100 or more. Melee range for pets on many NPCs is often higher than /shield range.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">12) Elemental Alacrity -</span>
<br />
VERY overpriced. It should be 3/3/3/3/3, not 3/6/9/12/15. Overall the AA cost on this is so high it’s prohibitive; maxing out our nuke crit AAs gives a better gain per AA than this. This AA should also apply to our pets nuking ability, not just melee. (Their nukes should be criting as well)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">13) Healing Adept/Gift/Adv Adept/Adv Gift -</span>
<br />
With the emphasis no longer on pet expendability but rather pet survival, it makes sense for Magicians to have these abilities now.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">14) Quick Damage -</span>
<br />
Why don't we have this? Without it, druids (a priest class) are actually out-nuking us consistently.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">15) Spell Casting Reinforcement/SCR Mastery -</span>
<br />
Why don't we have this? We have buffs just like anyone else
<br />

<br />
Possible new pet AA’s:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">16) Pet Command Mastery-</span>
<br />
This AA would give a mage additional control over their pets. Some nice features to have would be.
<br />

<br />
a) Stick to one mob (regardless of low health from a second mob the pet would not switch targets)
<br />

<br />
To fix the issues we have with the fire pet: 
<br />
b) Spell casting on/off
<br />
c) Melee on/off
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">17) Shared Attributes-</span>
<br />
This AA would allow the pet to benefit from the gear that the master (mage) has equipped. The pet would gain specific melee and spell casting enhancements just like PC's do.
<br />

<br />
 
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">3) Fix Fire pet [currently being discussed]</span>
<br />
Rytan has all details about fixing this pet. But to summarize:
<br />

<br />
One solution is to make it Warrior-class again.
<br />

<br />
The other solution is to tweak the AI of the pet, as well as specific fixes:
<br />
·  Nuke or melee only. If it has mana, it nukes and doesn't stop. 
<br />
·  Mana regen too slow. Its mana regen is abysmal. 
<br />
·  Too easy to unmezz mobs. When the pet starts to cast, it cannot be interrupted. 
<br />
·  Remove AOE’s. AOEs cause problems with aggro and mez breaks. 
<br />
·  Remove Debuffs. Often when it casts its various dispels it will take a debuff cast on the mob instead. 
<br />
·  Pet appear with the buffs already on it when it is summoned. When the pet is summoned it wastes considerable time initially buffing itself instead of engaging in combat. 
<br />
·  Remove any root/snare/cancel magic spells from a pet’s lineup which primarily makes a pet un-useable for groups and raids. Root causes shaky proximit aggro, snare is unreliable, and like said above the dispel causes problems.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">4) Improved Damage shield [incorrectly classified as done]</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Shield of Flame</span>
<br />
from 60 mana, 4 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 60 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Inferno Shield</span>
<br />
from 80 mana, 3.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 80 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Barrier of Combustion</span>
<br />
from 100 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 100 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Shield of Lava</span>
<br />
from 120 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 120 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Boon of Immolation (group)</span>
<br />
from 360 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 300 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Cadeau of Flame</span>
<br />
from 155 mana, 4.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 150 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Aegis of Ro (group)</span>
<br />
from 450 mana, 9 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 350 mana, 3 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Flameshield of Ro</span>
<br />
from 190 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 180 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Maelstrom of Ro (group)</span>
<br />
from 450 mana, 5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />
to 380 mana, 2.5 cast, 2.25 recast
<br />

<br />
These changes to the damage shields will insure, once and for all, that Magicians have the best and most efficient damage shields.
<br />

<br />
NOTE: Need Spell Casting Reinforcement AA to increase the duration, thus saving mana in the long run. 
<br />

<br />
 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">5) Streamline the item summoning process (more target summons) [currently being discussed]</span>
<br />

<br />
All summoned items should become targeted just like mod rods. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">6) Allow suspended pets to zone, OR allow pets to remain with their master while the master is invisible.  (Pet Issues/Requests) [updated request]</span>
<br />

<br />
While allowing pets to zone has been one of the biggest boosts in Magician power in  years, its inherent flaw is that you still lose your pet to invisibility. Suspended Minion allowed you to keep your pet when you went invisible, but zoning still kills it. One solution is to just allow suspended pets to zone with their master. The other (perhaps more favorable) solution is to prevent pets from being destroyed by Invisibility. Since pets are Beta-Neutral faction, they will not aggro anything anyway.
<br />

<br />
 
<br />

<br />
 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">7) Improve pet Heals. (Pet Issues/Requests) [currently being discussed]</span>
<br />
Pet heals need to be on-par with equivalent Beastlord heals HP-wise. The amount healed needs to be the same as beastlord heals, the cast time needs to be 3.75 seconds, and the recast time should be removed altogether. Higher level pet heals especially need a boost; in the time it takes to heal the pet, theres a high probability it is already dead. Also the amount currently healed is insufficient to equivalent level content (in Gates, for example, the 1200 HP healed from Planar Renewal is often less than one hit from random yard trash in Kod`Taz).
<br />
 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">8) Revamp pet focus availability. (Pet Issues/Requests) [updated request] </span>
<br />
Add a Minion of Darkness focus in Tier 3 Planes of Power zones (ideal loot for mages would be First Sergeant's Insignia, and/or Orb of Infinite Terror) to help bridge the gap between equivalent Ornate-geared Magicians and Elemental-geared Mages, pet wise.
<br />

<br />
Put the *Mancy focuses in the game. This will help bridge the gap between Ornate/Vex Thal-geared Magicians, Elemental-geared magicians, and Time-geared Magicians.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">9) COH useable in more zones. (make CoTH available in all corpse summoning zones) [currently being discussed]</span>
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">10) Better utility in groups and raids [detail was requested]</span>
<br />

<br />
a) Summoned snare pet weapons, and new proc weapons for the pet
<br />
b) Castable root as a form of crowd control
<br />
c) AE malosinia
<br />
d) Group CoH
<br />
e) Cross-zone CoH (i think its being implemented)
<br />
f) Malos</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
